After completion of economic life of EVMs/VVPATs, i.e. 15 years, EVMs/VVPATs are sent back to BEL/ECIL factories for destruction as per standard protocol. The following procedures are followed for destruction:
i. Printed Circuit Boards (PCBs) shall be separated from Plastic Housings;
ii. All components mounted on PCBs shall be removed/chopped off and crushed;
iii. The bare PCBs shall be cut into minimum 4 pieces and crushed;
iv. The remaining plastic assemblies/housing shall also be cut into 4 to 6 pieces and crushed;
v. Plastic waste shall be recycled to ensure that environment is protected;
vi. Entire process of the disposal/destruction should be videographed;
vii. Recording of videography shall be disposed of by BEL/ECIL only after confirmation from ECI.
viii. The guidelines/safeguards for destruction of electronic items, issued by the Pollution Control Board/Ministry of Environment and Forests etc. or any other law for the time being in force, shall be followed;
ix. It shall be ensured that e-wastes are channelized to registered dismantler or recycler;
x. A proper record of each unit destroyed/destructed should be maintained.
